The paper proposes a method for learning deep undirected graphical models using a non-ELBO objective and trained inference networks. This is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning, specifically in the areas of deep learning and probabilistic graphical models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the Bethe free energy approximation, which is a technique used in cryptography (cs.CR) and other areas of computer science, so this is also a possible sub-category.
